    "causal_summary": "The spec-kit generators disagree on spec-folder identity and the graph merge loses lineage. description.json stores a caller-base-relative specFolder from path.relative at folder-discovery.ts line 809 while graph metadata stores a specs-root-relative path, so the same folder carries two shapes. mergeGraphMetadata spreads the refreshed snapshot at graph-metadata-parser.ts lines 1149 to 1161, so a null-deriving parent_id from resolveParentId erases an existing non-null parent and a scoped scan replaces children_ids and deletes relationships. The fix adds a shared resolveSpecFolderIdentity helper consumed by both generators and a merge guard that reconciles parent_id as refreshed then existing then null and unions children_ids append-only, all behind a default-OFF flag with a grandfather report mode so existing files do not mass-fail.",
